From Andre Beck Subject Re Drawing colour pixmaps not rectangular In article Justin Kibell writes I am writing a program which needs to draw colour XPM pixmap files onto a background without having the borders show I cannot do xor as the colours all stuff I cannot use XCopyPlane as that is for single planes I want to be able to specify a colour in the pixmap to be used as the opaque Is this Games such as xjewel have the same How does the mouse pointer do it Any help would be helpful You wanna do Build a bitmap pixmap of depth one where all pixels you name opaque are that get copied and the others are Use this bitmap as the clip mask in the gc used for XCopyArea and remember to adjust the clip origin coordinates to the XCopyArea blit The Mouse pointer besides from that it is driven using RAMDAC analog mapping on most hardwares uses a mask But be warned blitting through a mask and especially moving around this mask is annoying slow on most it flickers even at o o o Brain Inside o o o o Andre' Beck ABPSoft mehl Andre Beck o o o